Key Match Events: Gelson Dala scored twice for Angola, completing his double from a resulting free-kick after Namibia defender received a red card.
Namibia defender Lubeni Haukongo received a red card shortly after Gelson opened the scoring.
Angola added a third goal through Mabululu in the second period.
Post-Match Reflections: Angola reached the Africa Cup of Nations (Afcon) quarterfinals with a comprehensive 3-0 victory over Namibia.
Namibia made their debut in the Cup of Nations knockout rounds but struggled to capitalize on early opportunities.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Angola's goalkeeper Neblu received a red card after handling the ball outside the box as he stopped Bethuel Muzeu’s chipped shot.
Deon Hotto’s resulting free kick was superbly saved by replacement keeper Antonio Dominique.
